OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1772422502
OL,3,CLabour parliamentarians urge UK
OL,4,CGovernment to oppose Rosebank oil field
OL,6,FIt comes as the UK Government
OL,7,Fcontinues to consider whether the
OL,8,Fdevelopment of the oil field can go
OL,9,Fahead ` with Labour now under mounting
OL,10,Fpressure after the loss of the Gorton
OL,11,Fand Denton by-election to the Greens
OL,12,Fon Thursday.
OL,14,FRosebank, which lies about 80 miles
OL,15,Fwest of Shetland, is the UK's largest
OL,16,Funtapped field, containing up to an
OL,17,Festimated 300 million barrels of oil.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,307,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F306A1772422502
OL,3,CLabour parliamentarians urge UK
OL,4,CGovernment to oppose Rosebank oil field
OL,6,FDrilling there was approved by the
OL,7,FConservative government in 2023 but
OL,8,Fwas then subject to a legal challenge
OL,9,Fin the wake of a Supreme Court ruling
OL,10,Fwhich said the emissions created from
OL,11,Fburning fossil fuels should be
OL,12,Fconsidered when granting permission
OL,13,Ffor new sites.
OL,15,FNow the decision on whether it can
OL,16,Fproceed lies with Labour ministers `
OL,17,Fwith some 16 Labour MPs having made
OL,18,Fplain their opposition to the
OL,19,Fdevelopment.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
